"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "5798: betrayal",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5798",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The treacherous exposing or deceiving of people by those they formerly trusted. It is usually associated with an enemy masquerading as a friend, or with a broken or abused relationship.  Betrayal was suffered by Jesus Christ and can be expected by his followers.</p>\n<h2>Betrayal is part of human experience</h2>\n<h3>Examples of those experiencing betrayal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:18\">JDG 16:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:17\">1SA 18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:26-2Sam19:27\">2SA 19:26–19:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:12-Ps55:14\">PSA 55:12–55:14</a> <em>Betrayal carries acute feelings for its victims</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:6\">JER 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:2\">LAM 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:19\">LAM 1:19</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of those murdered through betrayal</h3>\n<p>The power struggles of Israel's early kingship period gave rise to many bloody betrayals:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:27\">2SA 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam4:6\">2SA 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:15\">2SA 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:28-2Sam13:29\">2SA 13:28–13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:10\">2SA 20:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:8-1Kgs21:10\">1KI 21:8–21:10</a></p>\n<h2>Betrayal is seen as a particularly wicked act</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:1\">ISA 33:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:17\">1CH 12:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:9-Prov25:10\">PRO 25:9–25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:16-Isa24:17\">ISA 24:16–24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:24\">MAT 26:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:21\">MRK 14:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:22\">LUK 22:22</a></p>\n<h2>The betrayal of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Judas determines to betray Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14-Matt26:16\">MAT 26:14–26:16</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:10-Mark14:11\">MRK 14:10–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:3-Luke22:6\">LUK 22:3–22:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's knowledge of events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:21-Matt26:23\">MAT 26:21–26:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:18-Mark14:20\">MRK 14:18–14:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:17-Matt20:19\">MAT 20:17–20:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:33-Mark10:34\">MRK 10:33–10:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:21\">LUK 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:11\">JHN 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:18\">JHN 13:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:21-John13:27\">JHN 13:21–13:27</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is betrayed by a kiss</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47-Matt26:49\">MAT 26:47–26:49</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43-Mark14:45\">MRK 14:43–14:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:47-Luke22:48\">LUK 22:47–22:48</a> <em>The kiss featured in several betrayals as part of feigned friendship (see e.g., <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:9-2Sam20:10\">2Sa 20:9–10</a> and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:6\">Pr 27:6</a>).</em></p>\n<h3>The betrayer's remorse</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:5\">MAT 27:3–27:5</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Betrayal may be part of Christian experience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:21\">MAT 10:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12\">MRK 13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:16\">LUK 21:16</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:25\">DAN 7:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:35-Matt10:36\">MAT 10:35–10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:6\">MIC 7:6</a></p>\n<h2>Betrayal as a sign of the end times</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:10\">MAT 24:10</a></p>\n<h2>God never betrays those who trust in him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:33\">PSA 89:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:8\">PSA 118:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:1\">PSA 125:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:25\">PRO 29:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:3-Isa26:4\">ISA 26:3–26:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a></p>",
